nib.text:
Over 3,400 customers lost power in Whittier after a car thief collided with an electric pole Monday afternoon.

A 911 caller reported a collision with injuries soon after 3 p.m. near E. 26th Street & Nicollet Avenue S.

Citizen user video on the scene showed a downed power line.

First responders reported a man stole a vehicle and collided with the pole, then fled on foot.

Firefighters blocked traffic at Blaisdell Avenue.

Xcel Energy confirmed one outage in the area began shortly after 3 p.m. affecting 2,144 customers. It was forecast to be resolved around 5 p.m.

Xcel Energy confirmed another outage nearby began around 3:30 p.m. and affected at leat 1,346 customers. See the outage map [here](https://www.outagemap-xcelenergy.com/outagemap/). The outage was forecast to be repaired  by 6:41 p.m.
